    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but isnt the whole point of freedom of religion to protect people from being forced to do things that go against their deepest convictions? if the state can just force everyone to comply with everything, doesn't that basically erase religious freedom in practice? how do you reconcile that with the idea of protecting individual rights?",
